pageType: content
background:
  type: solid
  color: "$dbg"
elements:
  - elementId: kicker
    elementType: text
    bounds: [64, 36, 400, 16]
    content:
      style: "$dKick"
      wrap: false
      text: 01 · THE LAST MILE
  - elementId: top-right
    elementType: text
    bounds: [660, 36, 236, 16]
    content:
      style: "$dKick"
      align: [right, top]
      wrap: false
      text: W&V · WORKSPACEALBERTA
  - elementId: h1
    elementType: text
    bounds: [64, 88, 832, 54]
    content:
      style: "$dDisp"
      fontSize: 44
      wrap: false
      text: AI promised 5X productivity.
  - elementId: h2
    elementType: text
    bounds: [64, 152, 520, 156]
    content:
      style: "$dDisp"
      fontSize: 44
      color: "$dink40"
      text: |
        <p>Most small businesses got a <span style="color:$ember">chatbot</span> that writes mediocre marketing copy.</p>
  - elementId: body
    elementType: text
    bounds: [64, 330, 500, 120]
    content:
      style: "$dBody"
      fontSize: 15
      text: |
        <p>The model is not the bottleneck. The connection is. Government tender databases are the perfect example: the work is public, the demand is real, but the discovery process is still awkward enough that good companies miss good opportunities.</p>
  - elementId: photo
    elementType: image
    bounds: [612, 136, 284, 340]
    src: media/sophie-okowinski-bren-gun.jpg
    fit: {mode: cover}
    border: {style: solid, width: 1, color: "$dhair2"}
  - elementId: photo-overlay
    elementType: shape
    bounds: [612, 136, 284, 340]
    shapeName: rect
    fill: {type: solid, color: "#0a080759"}
  - elementId: caption
    elementType: text
    bounds: [612, 484, 284, 26]
    content:
      style: "$dLabel"
      lineHeight: 1.4
      text: Sophie O'Kowinski, John Inglis Co., 1943 · Library and Archives Canada
